I retired in February 1977 at the age of sixty five years after a full working life of fifty one years, of which thirty three years were spent in the Hull Fire Brigade. When I retired I wondered how I would settle down to a more stereotyped and tranquil sort of life but I was determined not to become chair bound. Just previous to retiring I moved from Hull to Gilberdyke and here I found scope for a more varied sort of life.
By becoming a Parish Councillor and a School Governor new horizons were opened out for me. Today I could be involved in meeting Community Improvement representatives regarding improving amenities in the village,
